{"key":"processedPost-17114298","value":{"id":17114298,"first":17102419,"last":17132283,"when":1351395474,"utime":"10/28/12 06:37 AM","content":"The pictures below from left to right show how I load mine.&nbsp; Fold the bags over with tyvek sleeves in each one, and then place hardware cloth over the top. Be sure to put something between the bags so the steam can totally surround each bag.&nbsp; I use jar lids. Then, place angle iron over the hardware cloth to keep the bags from unfolding.&nbsp; Seal after inoculation.<br />Many commercial autoclaves are not suitable.&nbsp; Make sure it's not going to open a solenoid valve at the end of the cycle to dump steam.&nbsp; If it does, all your bags will burst.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/10-007/672788559-20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_014a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/10-007/672788559-thumb_20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_014a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/10-007/672788614-20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_015a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/10-007/672788614-thumb_20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_015a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/10-007/672788668-20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_016a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/10-007/672788668-thumb_20_Feb_2010_Barrel_sterilizer_016a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/11-14/250136916-Boiler_and_loaded_sterilizer.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/11-14/250136916-th